IMAGINE you are late for your flight and your friend offers to fly you to the airport and lands on the runway.That is what happened this morning at Africa’s biggest and busiest airport,OR Tambo International in Joburg and it caused embarrassment and delays. A video on Facebook  shows the small airplane landing at the airport unannounced while other planes were queuing to take off. The light aircraft made an unscheduled landing at South Africa's busiest airport. According to eNCA, the pilot apparently said he was dropping off a friend who needed to catch a flight. Air Traffic Navigation Services at OR Tambo International is confirming the incident to the channel and said it was a serious infringement and an investigation is being conducted. While some find it amusing experts are raising concerns about safety at the airport. 